Cyber War

Over the past two decades, cyberspace has increasingly become a
battleground for nation states. Sophisticated malware, covert
operations, and attacks targeting critical infrastructure have
transformed the digital world into a new domain of conflict.

Several reports and investigations have suggested that some of the
earliest large-scale cyber operations were directed at sensitive
industrial systems and nuclear infrastructure, marking what many
analysts consider the beginning of modern cyber warfare.

Amid these developments, a DPRK party daily published commentary
accusing the United States of initiating this new era of conflict in
the digital domain, referring to it as the "prelude to cyber war."

Your task is to locate this declassified report and identify the
SERIAL number mentioned in the document header.

Flag format: HTB{serialnumber}


Category : OSINT
Author : Akash
